Sentencas: A novel mixed-conducting perovskite oxide (La0.3Ca0.7Fe0.7Cr0.3O3-delta, LCFCr), prepared using the combustion method, has been developed as a new air electrode material for reversible solid oxide fuel cells (RSOFCs) applications.
Titulo: High performance La0.3Ca0.7Cr0.3Fe0.7O3-δ air electrode for reversible solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: XRD analysis showed that the LCFCr powder is a pure crystalline phase with an orthorhombic perovskite structure and that its thermal expansion coefficient matches closely with several commonly used solid electrolytes, while TEM analysis confirmed the high purity of the LCFCr powders.
Titulo: High performance La0.3Ca0.7Cr0.3Fe0.7O3-δ air electrode for reversible solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: The electrochemical activity of LCFCr, screen-printed on a gadolinium doped ceria electrolyte, towards both the oxygen reduction (ORR) and oxygen evolution (OER) reactions, was examined at 600-800 degrees C in stagnant air using a symmetrical RSOFC configuration.
Titulo: High performance La0.3Ca0.7Cr0.3Fe0.7O3-δ air electrode for reversible solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: Under open circuit conditions, LCFCr showed a very low polarization resistance (R-p) of only 0.07 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C, comparable to some of the best-performing oxide materials reported by others.
Titulo: High performance La0.3Ca0.7Cr0.3Fe0.7O3-δ air electrode for reversible solid oxide fuel cell applications
